                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/11967: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-12T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 12, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 12—5:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>680. Department’s 470, June 10, 10 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]. I
                    delivered the oral message and <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to Marshal
                    Pétain at 6:00 this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Report of interview follows.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
